Description for the Student Grade Manager 
The Student Grade Manager is a user-friendly application designed to help you efficiently track and manage student grades. 
This program provides a simple and intuitive graphical user interface (GUI) for adding grades, calculating average grades, and displaying overall performance metrics such as letter grades and GPA.

Features:
Add Student:
Enter the student's name and add it to the system.
Add Grades:
Enter the subject and the corresponding grade for each assignment or exam.
Grades can range from 0 to 100.
Display Grades:
View all the entered grades for each subject.
Display Overall Grade:
Calculate and display the student's average grade.
Convert the average grade into a GPA.
Display the corresponding letter grade.
How to Use:
Add a Student:
Start by entering the student's name in the provided text field and click the "Add Student" button.
Add Grades:
Enter the subject and grade in their respective fields and click the "Add Grade" button.
Ensure that the grade is a valid number between 0 and 100.
View Grades:
Click the "Display Grades" button to view all the grades entered for the student.
View Overall Performance:
Click the "Display Overall Grade" button to see the student's average grade, GPA, and letter grade.
Technical Details:
Programming Language: Python
GUI Framework: Tkinter
Data Handling: The program uses a class-based approach to store and manage student data.
Example Usage Scenario:
Imagine a teacher who wants to keep track of their students' grades throughout the semester. 
By using the Student Grade Manager, the teacher can easily add grades for each subject, monitor the student's progress, and quickly calculate the overall performance at the end of the term.
This ensures a streamlined and organized approach to grade management, reducing the likelihood of errors and saving valuable time.
